				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://discuss.userland.com/msgReader$19739&quot;&gt;Eric Kidd's open&lt;/a&gt; source dilemma."/>
				<outline text="Next Radio UserLand feature: Chat. (Using the outliner of course.) I did my &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/images/chatWorksFirstTime.gif&quot;&gt;first chat&lt;/a&gt; at about 8:45PM with David Brown. I'll write more about it tomorrow."/>
				<outline text="Today's song: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.50megs.com/webfitz/Lyrics/1968/721968.html&quot;&gt;Dream A Little Dream Of Me&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://radiodiscuss.userland.com/discuss/msgReader$562&quot;&gt;Jeremy Bowers&lt;/a&gt; has done something very innovative with Radio UserLand. He's turned his history.xml file into a weblog. It's time for a callback so users' scripts can catch the history flow and turn it into any kind of XMLization they want. "/>
				<outline text="BTW, this is what I meant the other day about having a tool to go with every XML format. The outlineDocument format puts the power in users hands because there's a tool with an easy hood-lift, you don't need a degree in rocket science to figure it out, it just sneaks up on you. &quot;If he can do it, so can I.&quot;"/>
				<outline text="OK, now here's a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/images/jeremysHistoryAsWeblog.gif&quot;&gt;screen shot&lt;/a&gt; of Jeremy's &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ourfavoritesongs.com/users/irights@jerf.org/history.xml&quot;&gt;history.xml&lt;/a&gt; file, integrated with the user hierarchy on OurFavoriteSongs.Com. The XML is a constantly changing, so don't expect to see exactly what's in the screen shot."/>
				<outline text="It's an exciting time! Our users are trying things before we thought of them. &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.egroups.com/message/radio-userland/830&quot;&gt;Yesterday&lt;/a&gt; Aaron Swarz tried to open &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/xml/currentOutline.xml&quot;&gt;Scripting News&lt;/a&gt; in Radio UserLand. It almost worked!"/>
				<outline text="BTW, &lt;a href=&quot;http://swartzfam.com/aaron/&quot;&gt;Aaron&lt;/a&gt; is 14. He's the next &lt;a href=&quot;http://wmf.editthispage.com/&quot;&gt;Wes Felter&lt;/a&gt;, imho. &quot;;-&gt;&quot; (The next &lt;a href=&quot;http://scriptingnews.userland.com/pictures/viewer$890&quot;&gt;Woz&lt;/a&gt;, again imho.)"/>
				<outline text="I got an email from Aaron correcting me. He's 13, not 14! I told him that I first met Wes when he was roughly that age. I didn't meet Woz until he was in his 30s. (He just turned 50 last week.)"/>
