					<outline text="I spoke briefly on the phone this afternoon with Clay Shirky, columnist for Feed, professor and startup-advisor. He wrote an &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nytimes.com/00/07/15/oped/15shir.html&quot;&gt;op-ed piece&lt;/a&gt; in the NY Times about Napster that remains one of my anthems. We see eye-to-eye on where this is going, and the importance of the Internet's version of radio. He also pointed out that Napster has more members than AOL. An interesting statistic for sure. (The power of music, again.)"/>
