				<outline text="MacWEEK: &lt;a href=&quot;http://macweek.zdnet.com/2000/08/06/0810jcwnetscape.html&quot;&gt;Netscape's woeful Mac support&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="Wes Felter's distributed file sharing &lt;a href=&quot;http://wmf.editthispage.com/distributedFileSharing&quot;&gt;comparison&lt;/a&gt;, including Napster, Gnutella, Publius, Freenet and Mojo Nation."/>
				<outline text="BTW, a few of the &lt;a href=&quot;http://davenet.userland.com/1996/08/28/BeeSeason&quot;&gt;bees&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://davenet.userland.com/1999/07/20/theBeesAreBack&quot;&gt;are&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://davenet.userland.com/1998/08/26/allAboutBees&quot;&gt;back&lt;/a&gt;. The early ones. The scouts. In a couple of weeks they'll be swarming over everything that smells like bee food, which, unfortunately, includes people."/>
				<outline text="A new feature, &lt;a href=&quot;http://radiodiscuss.userland.com/howUpstreamingWorks&quot;&gt;upstreaming&lt;/a&gt;, was released to Radio UserLand testers. &quot;Upstreaming is the automatic movement of content off your workstation to a non-changing location that's publicly accessible.&quot;"/>
				<outline text="I have four playlists in my upstreamed &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ourfavoritesongs.com/users/dave@userland.com/sets/&quot;&gt;folder&lt;/a&gt;. Next step, linking between outlines. To get that process started, every user's directory needs a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ourfavoritesongs.com/users/dave@userland.com/directory.xml&quot;&gt;directory&lt;/a&gt; of the files it contains. "/>
				<outline text="About firewalls. In general Radio UserLand &lt;i&gt;will not&lt;/i&gt; work behind a firewall. We are not, with this product, working around firewalls in any way. That's a deliberate decision. Firewalls are designed to stop people from running servers. In 2000 that means you can't be part of a peer-to-peer community. "/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://discuss.userland.com/msgReader$19666&quot;&gt;A patent story&lt;/a&gt; so simple a child could understand why they are bad news for environments where people share ideas freely. "/>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://release1.userland.com/&quot;&gt;A really nice redesign&lt;/a&gt; at Kevin Werbach's weblog companion to the Release 1.0 newsletter."/>
				<outline text="An amazing thing. Every Sting song I've never heard is a big hit with me. Today I'm digging &lt;a href=&quot;http://stingetc.com/lyrics/brandnew.html&quot;&gt;Brand New Day&lt;/a&gt;. I've lived that. Been there. Music gets to places no other artform can, for me at least. Thanks!"/>
